What's adapted vs. dropped
--------------------------

Kept from musl:
- The atoi algorithm: skip whitespace, optional sign, accumulate
  as a negative number to avoid INT_MIN overflow.

Dropped:
- musl's `__atoi_l` locale-aware variant and `weak_alias` glue.
  This library is C-locale only.
- atol/atoll/strtol/strtoul size variants — atoi covers the
  pedagogical ground; the others would just duplicate the
  algorithm with wider types.
